# Security Considerations

This document outlines security considerations for the Bitcoin Converter API.

## Authentication and Authorization

- Describe how authentication and authorization are handled in your API.
- Explain the use of API keys, tokens, or any other authentication mechanisms.

## Input Validation

- Discuss the importance of input validation to prevent common security vulnerabilities like SQL injection or Cross-Site Scripting (XSS).
- Mention how user input is sanitized and validated before processing.

## Rate Limiting

- Implement rate limiting to protect against brute force attacks or abuse.
- Define the rate-limiting policies and mechanisms in place.

## Data Encryption

- Describe how sensitive data is encrypted, both at rest and in transit.
- Specify the encryption algorithms and protocols used.

## Error Handling

- Implement secure error handling to avoid exposing sensitive information.
- Provide guidelines on logging errors for internal use without leaking details to clients.

## Reporting Security Issues

If you discover a security issue, please report it to [security@example.com](mailto:security@example.com).
